    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11 T 41/8½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-06">6 <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >April</hi>, 1915</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Thank you for showing me
                    these.</p>
                <p>I will keep Lansing’s note about the Thrasher case until we get the information
                    we have asked for and until I can see and meditate upon what you are to put in
                    writing of your own views; and will give my thoughts time to settle before
                    allowing myself to form a conclusion. I feel, as you do, the greatest anxiety
                    about the matter.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
